HEADWORD: Panic-struck
<hw>Pan"ic-struck`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Struck with a panic, or sudden
fear; thrown into a state of intense fear; <as>as, trying to keep back
the <ex>panic-stricken</ex> crowd</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> panicky, petrified, terrified, frightened.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

